English Version

AlinOs-for-android Open Source License Statement

1. Project Overview

This project is an early prototype integration based on termux/termux-app. No single open source license applies to the whole project. Different code modules are governed by multiple licenses, including MIT, GPLv3, Apache 2.0, etc.

Critical Warning:

You must independently review the original license texts of all upstream components, especially the viral nature of GPLv3. The author provides no warranty of commercial usability and assumes no liability for your failure to comply with third-party license terms. If you plan to distribute (including release APK or source code) or commercially use this project, you must personally verify the mandatory license requirements of each module.

1. Code Modules and License Breakdown (Reference Only - Always Check Upstream)

Module Path or Component: app/src/main/java/alin/android/alinos
Upstream Project: Original code
License: MIT License
Description: See appendix at the end of this file.

Module Path or Component: app/src/main/java/com/termux/app
Upstream Project: termux/termux-app
License: GPLv3 only
Description: Strong Copyleft. Distributing this part forces the entire project to be open source under GPLv3.

Module Path or Component: terminal-emulator / terminal-view
Upstream Project: jackpal/Android-Terminal-Emulator
License: Apache License 2.0
Description: Attribution required.

Module Path or Component: termux-shared (core subdirectory com/termux/shared/termux/)
Upstream Project: termux/termux-app
License: GPLv3 only (partial)
Description: The main body is under MIT License, but the above core subdirectory is bound by GPLv3 only.

The above information is for quick reference only and may be incomplete or inaccurate. You must check the actual LICENSE files in each upstream repository.

1. User Obligations

Self-audit: You must verify the license terms of all upstream code you use, especially copyleft licenses (GPLv3, AGPL, etc.). Assume all risks: If you violate GPLv3 (e.g., distributing core modules in closed source), you bear full legal responsibility. This statement does not replace professional legal counsel.

